  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "Q6rIJ1CF5CinVy4oBFY0XFFNr4g=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:34.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Epoch feeds: SDK gap blocks adoption\n\nSwarm epoch feeds (paper \u00a74.3.4) index SOC feeds by `(time, level)` instead of sequence number, giving a cold reader O(log age) lookup of the latest-as-of-time update \u2014 directly useful for the cross-Bee `publishPublicProfile` staleness we see on 2.7.x (receivers serve pre-update versions for minutes).\n\nBut they are not implementable today:\n\n- **bee-js 11.1.1**: the `Epoch { time, level }` type exists, but `findNextIndex`, `updateFeedWithReference`, and `downloadFeedUpdate` all take a sequence-`FeedIndex`. Epoch support is vestigial.\n- **Bee 2.7.x HTTP**: `/feeds/{owner}/{topic}` is sequence-only.\n- **Custom path**: would require bypassing feed helpers and manipulating SOCs directly \u2014 epoch lookup algorithm, custom chunk address derivation per level, grid traversal reader. Feasible but significant scope.\n\n**Decision:** DEFER. Reconsider when bee-js or Bee exposes epoch lookup natively. Not worth custom chunk-layer work right now.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:34.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:34.000Z"
    }
  },
